    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "--- name: many-claudes-disambiguate description: \"The user",
      "uuid": "dbd235f502c0487488211c459e8a2efa",
      "x": -1620.2738877070478,
      "y": 1733.296414751736,
      "width": 593.0,
      "height": 161.0,
      "z_value": -9.92800000000004,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "  Runs several distinct Claude implementations, (almost) all just named \\\"Claude\\\" \u2014 when a request says \\\"Claude\\\"/\\\"the proofreader\\\"/\\\"ClaudeNode\\\", confirm WHICH one before acting\" metadata: node_type: memory type: user originSessionId: 85bb8623-2c0a-4983-8613-5c167d7def0d hook: | - [Many Claudes \u2014 check which one](user_many_claudes_disambiguate.md) \u2014 several distinct Claudes, nearly all named \"Claude\"; confirm which is meant before acting ---"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "b8093edd8bb847378cacf39e5d85e881",
      "x": -999999.0,
      "y": -999999.0,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 148.0,
      "z_value": 0.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "label": "Now call `_restore_pinned_preview` after the session loads:",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "How to apply",
      "uuid": "0a6d5a024f4b4607bb25e9baf23068db",
      "x": -231.18719212962844,
      "y": 1770.2868897830406,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 146.0,
      "z_value": -9.924000000000042,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "  When a \"Claude\" reference is ambiguous, a quick \"which Claude?\" beats\nacting on the wrong one. Don't resolve it by assumption."
    },
