    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "709f72ee0fee4d32b84e93c33db397db",
      "x": -999999.0,
      "y": -999999.0,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 596.0,
      "z_value": 0.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "label": "Done. What persists across restarts:\n\n- `ui.preview_pinned = true/false` \u2014 whether the panel is pinned\n- `ui.preview_pinned_path = \"/abs/path/to/image.jpg\"` \u2014 which image was pinned, matched by `source_path`\n\nOn startup, after the session loads, `_restore_pinned_preview` walks the scene, finds the `ImageNode` with the matching path, loads its pixmap into the panel, and silently re-engages the pin button (via `blockSignals` so it doesn't re-trigger the save unnecessarily). If the image node is no longer on the canvas the pin simply doesn't restore.",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Distinct ones surfaced so far: - ClaudeNode: the",
      "uuid": "5da29630c9144c069c52aec9c9176843",
      "x": -778.3437680944924,
      "y": 1791.8313882378654,
      "width": 497.0,
      "height": 176.0,
      "z_value": -9.926000000000041,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "  In-Intricate, sidebar-loadable node; a file-parser over the local .claude transcripts (see [[claudenode-is-file-parser]]). Not an API chat. - The proofreader \u2014 a separate Claude implementation for writing analysis (rules in shared_braincell). It IS a core feature of The Majestic (which is part of Intricate) \u2014 do NOT treat it as isolated-from-Intricate; that framing was an earlier misread. - Sakura Claude \u2014 at least this one carries a distinguishing name. - ...and more; assume the roster grows."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "And we literally talk to Claude from inside the graph",
