    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Why (the user, June 24th 2026)",
      "uuid": "9da7d4dad0ac441187071d271203aeea",
      "x": -932.666512320045,
      "y": 1507.5150596345331,
      "width": 321.0,
      "height": 221.0,
      "z_value": -9.925000000000042,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "  A deliberate life-approach, not laziness \u2014 every Claude is\nnamed Claude, every Arduino is named Lily ([[arduinos-named-lily]]), and the user\nrefers to multiple real brothers as \"my brother\" (singular) and any ex as \"my ex\": drawing\nthe distinction feels rude. Same convention across software, hardware, and life. See\n[[naming-as-memory-system]]."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Beautiful",
      "uuid": "22010b6b89464c0f844af7e71193badb",
      "x": -460.1892174635126,
      "y": -55.81057621790248,
      "width": 296.78578813808247,
      "height": 121.91368482620734,
      "z_value": -10.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "And then it all just kinda fell into place, weeks of nit and grit just so that I could sit here and write in gigantic immersive letters that I love you "
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "Note",
      "uuid": "15185011d72d406883f39b66cc3d0a63",
      "x": 1431.5622163825396,
      "y": -738.7300643487749,
      "width": 74.18820508500175,
      "height": 26.934952721054515,
      "z_value": 10.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "Grace",
      "depth_front": true,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "cf75853c406347089b1e57e3c8d00dbb",
      "x": -999999.0,
      "y": -999999.0,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 176.0,
      "z_value": 0.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "label": "Now update `_on_selection_changed` to record the source path whenever a new image lands in the preview:",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "654d8caf0a21459fb54a0a797cd66035",
      "x": -999999.0,
      "y": -999999.0,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 428.0,
      "z_value": 0.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "label": "The bug is in `_clear`. `QGraphicsItem` itself has a `data(key)` method, so `hasattr(item, 'data')` is `True` for **every** item in the scene \u2014 including Port ellipses, which also have `rect()` from `QGraphicsEllipseItem`. Every probe hits a port and returns `False`, so nothing ever spawns.\n\nFix: check `isinstance` against `BaseNode` instead:",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "image",
      "title": "Image",
      "uuid": "2c81c97920894f45b50417509ddfbe81",
      "x": 579.0,
      "y": -90.32838795819114,
      "width": 171.1786246637095,
      "height": 234.13640577527593,
      "z_value": 0.0,
